DoubleVectorProperty.Documentation:
Exponent λ in blend strength S = (1 - g/x)^λ with g/x in (0, 1), clamped to [0.1, 10]. g and x are
weighted geodesic lengths. λ > 1 makes the falloff more convex (steeper near the outer edge g→x);
λ < 1 more concave (gentler).

StringVectorProperty.Documentation:
vtkDoubleArray on output when Geodesic smooth influence range > 0: 1 on strict (mask 0)
vertices; in the geodesic band, S = (1 - g/x)^λ only if the vertex is actually displaced (R > d);
otherwise 0. Empty name falls back to StentGeodesicSmoothStrength.
